geo:siteIdentification.geo:notes: The antenna is 7.5 m above the ground. IGS Reference Frame Station in the Geodetical Observatory Wettzell. In addition and parallel an ASHTECH Z12T Metronome GPS Receiver, Four character ID WTZA, on pillar 1204, Domes No. 14201M013, a JAVAD TRE_G3TH DELTA GPS+GLONASS Receiver, Four character ID WTZZ, on pillar 1205, Domes No. 14201M014, a JPS LEGACY GPS+GLONASS Receiver, Four character ID WT21, on pillar 21, DOMES No. 14201M021, and a SEPT POLARX2 GPS Receiver, Four character ID WTZS, DOMES No. 14201M015 are observing. Prior we observed here in the Geodetical Observatory Wettzell with a TI-4100, a MiniMac 2816 AT, a Rogue SNR-800, our # 1200, Four Character ID WETT, Domes No. 14201M009, a 3SNAV R101 GPS+GLONASS Receiver, Four character ID WTZG, on pillar 1203, Domes No. 14201M012, a TRIMBLE 4000 SSI, Four character ID WTZT, on pillar 1201, Domes No. 14201M011, a JPS LEGACY GPS+GLONASS Receiver, Four character ID WTZJ,on pillar 1203, DOMES No. 14201M012, a TPS NETG3 GPS+GLONASS Receiver Four character ID WTZL, on pillar 1206, Domes No. 14201M022. Further informations and effective dates see section 5 and 7.
